    "Instead of key scheduling, round-dependent constants are used to reduce software overload.",
    "LED:The LED Block Cipher is an SPN based on AES.",
    "Encryption is done in 48-slice increments with XORing of the key in between [70].",
    "An individual round is formed by XORing an AES panache round.",
    "A key of 16 bytes is divided into two subkeys of 8 bytes each, whereas a key of 8 bytes is XORed with an internal state."
